Reducing package count has several practical benefits across the container platform.
The Ripple Effect of Small Images:
	•	Faster Builds and Deployments: Smaller images reduce the overall build context and layer compression overhead, enabling faster LightSpeed builds and quicker Harness deployments.
	•	Infrastructure Efficiency: Smaller images require fewer resources to push, pull, and store within container registries such as Artifactory. This leads to:
	⁃	Faster read and write operations in the artifactory
	⁃	Reduced network bandwidth consumption during image distribution
	⁃	Lower Artifactory storage usage
	⁃	Faster artifact replication across environments
	•	Developer Experience:  Fewer packages result in fewer Renovate pull requests and fewer GEMs or exploitable CVEs detected during VSaaS scans, reducing the likelihood of LightSpeed builds or Harness deployments failing security gating checks.


