Choosing the Right Base Image: Minimal vs Micro


UBI9 Minimal
The goal is to pick the smallest base image your application can support.

Feature
Includes microdnf, a lightweight package manager similar to yum/dnf.
When to use
Use UBI9 Minimal when you need to install additional dependencies during the Docker build process while still maintaining a smaller image footprint.
Summary
Good balance between flexibility and security

UBI9 Micro
Feature
No package manager and an extremely small runtime footprint.
When to use
Ideal for:
	•	Internet facing or internally sensitive applications that require hardened production images. 
	•	short-lived jobs requiring fast startup
Summary
Maximum security, minimum footprint




